doctype html
html
	head
		title scrumoji | About | An emoji guide for your agile communciation
		link(rel="canonical", href="https://scrumoji.org/about")
		style
			include ../../dist/css/style.css
		include _includes/_meta.pug
	body
		include _includes/_icons.pug
		include _includes/_nav.pug
		header.header
			include ../images/scrumoji.svg
			h2 An emoji guide for your agile communciation
		main.wrap
			section
				h1 About
				p #[strong scrumoji is an emoji guide for agile communication]. Aims to be a standardization cheatsheet - guide for using #[a(href="http://emoji.muan.co") emojis] on Agile communication messages.
				p #[strong Using emojis] provides an #[strong easy way] of #[strong identifying the purpose] or intention with only looking at the emojis used. As there are a lot of different emojis I found the need of creating a guide that can help to use emojis easier.
				p This project is Open Source, that means everyone can participate, suggesting, discussing and adding new emojis. Take a look at the #[a(href="#contributing-scrumoji") contributing section] and #[a(href="https://github.com/oschrenk/scrumoji/blob/master/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md") the guidelines for contributing].
				div
					a.btn.btn-pink(href="https://github.com/oschrenk/scrumoji/")
						svg.icon.icon-star
							use(xlink:href='#icon-star')
						| GitHub
					a.btn.btn-pink(href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=scrumoji%20%E2%80%93%20An%20%23emoji%20guide%20for%20your%20Agile%20communication%20by%20%40oschrenk%20%F0%9F%98%8D%F0%9F%98%9C&url=https://scrumoji.org", target="_blank")
						svg.icon.icon-twitter
							use(xlink:href='#icon-twitter')
						| Tweet
			section
				h1#contributing-scrumoji Contributing to scrumoji
				p Contributing to scrumoji it's a piece of cake üç∞! This project it's a static website built with #[i Pug, SCSS, Gulp and ES6]. All the scrumojis displayed are rendered from a JSON file. Before submitting any pull request, please follow the next steps:
				ol
					li #[a(href="https://github.com/oschrenk/scrumoji/issues/new") Create an issue] filling the template.
					li After discussing the idea, feature or suggestion, #[a(href="https://github.com/oschrenk/scrumoji/fork") fork scrumoji]
					li Create a new branch with the feature name. (Eg: add-emoji-deploy, fix-website-header)
					li Make your changes and send a #[a(href="https://help.github.com/articles/creating-a-pull-request/") pull request ].
				div
					a.btn.btn-pink(href="https://github.com/oschrenk/scrumoji/blob/master/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md") Contributing guidelines

		include _includes/_footer.pug
	script
		include ../scripts/main.js
